{"sessionKey":"42nd2nd08","paragraphs":[{"html":"<a name=\"StartOfColumns\"></a><b><i>The House met at 1:30 p.m.</i></b>","index":"00000","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> O Eternal and Almighty God, from Whom all power and wisdom come,\nwe are assembled here before Thee to frame such laws as may tend to the welfare\nand prosperity of our province. Grant, O merciful God, we pray Thee, that we\nmay desire only that which is in accordance with Thy will, that we may seek it\nwith wisdom and know it with certainty and accomplish it perfectly for the\nglory and honour of Thy name and for the welfare of all our people. Amen.","index":"00001","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Please be seated. Good afternoon, everybody. ","index":"00002","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Reg </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874808\">Helwer</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Central Services):</b> I&nbsp;&nbsp;move, seconded by the Minister of\nFinance (Mr.&nbsp;&nbsp;Fielding), that Bill 9, The Public Services\nSustainability Amendment Act, be now read a first time. ","index":"00003","speaker":"Reg Helwer"},{"html":"<b><i>Motion\npresented.</i></b> ","index":"00004","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Helwer:</b> The Public Services Sustainability Amendment\nAct establishes a sustainable fiscal framework for the private sector\ncollective bargaining. Amendments to The Public Services Sustainability Act are\nnow being introduced to address some of the suggestions from employers and&nbsp;&nbsp;unions.","index":"00005","speaker":"Reg Helwer"},{"html":"����� We\ncontinue to encourage collective bargaining and will continue to encourage\nemployers and unions to work together to find innovative ideas that will ensure\nsustainability of our public services. ","index":"00006","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? Agreed? <i>[Agreed]</i>�\n","index":"00007","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Ron </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874810\">Schuler</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Infrastructure):</b> Madam Speaker, I move, seconded by the Minister of\nCrown Services (Mr. Wharton), that Bill 14, The Public Sector Construction\nProjects (Tendering) Act, be now read for a first time. ","index":"00008","speaker":"Ron Schuler"},{"html":"<b><i>Motion presented.</i></b> ","index":"00009","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nSchuler:</b> Madam Speaker, I'm pleased to introduce Bill 14, The Public Sector\nConstruction Projects (Tendering) Act, as part of the Manitoba government's\n100-Day Action Plan. ","index":"00010","speaker":"Ron Schuler"},{"html":"����� This\nlegislation will create a fairer and more competitive bidding process for\npublicly funded construction projects by ensuring that public sector entities\ntendering processes are unbiased with respect to the unionization status of\nbidders and their employees. ","index":"00011","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00012","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nScott </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874812\">Fielding</a></b><b>�(Minister of Finance):</b> I\nmove,&nbsp;&nbsp;seconded by the Minister of Municipal Relations (Ms. Squires),\nthat Bill 12, The Workplace Safety and Health Amendment Act, be now read a\nfirst time. ","index":"00013","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"<b><i>Motion presented.</i></b> ","index":"00014","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Fielding:</b> I'm pleased to\nintroduce Bill 12, The Workplace Safety and Health Amendment Act. ","index":"00015","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"����� The proposal will amend The\nWorkplace Safety and Health Act to eliminate the chief prevention officer\nposition, increase maximum penalties for offences under the act and approve\ncollection mechanisms for additional penalties levelled by the court, restrict\ncomplaints that frivolous�were not being made for specific timeframe, change\nterminology used in the act to reduce confusion with other statutes. ","index":"00016","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00017","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nScott </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874814\">Fielding</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Finance):</b> I move, seconded by the Minister of Health, that Bill 16, The\nLabour Relations Amendment Act, now be read a first time. ","index":"00018","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"<b><i>Motion\npresented.</i></b> ","index":"00019","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nFielding:</b> I'm pleased to introduce Bill 16, The Labour Relations Amendment\nAct. ","index":"00020","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"����� This\nproposal will amend The Labour Relations Act to facilitate the transition of\n'concilitation'�'concileration' in grievance to mediation functions to the\nprivate sector, eliminate the requirements due by annual review of the act's\nprovisions, respect in the settlement of collective agreements and give\nLieutenant Governor-in-Council regulation-making authority to establish fees\nfor services provided by the Manitoba Labour Board. <b>�</b>�","index":"00021","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00022","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nScott </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874816\">Fielding</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Finance):</b> I move,&nbsp;&nbsp;seconded by the Minister of Families (Mrs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stefanson),\nthat Bill 21, The Workers Compensation Amendment Act, be now read a first time.\n","index":"00023","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"<b><i>Motion\npresented.</i></b> ","index":"00024","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nFielding:</b> I am pleased to introduce Bill 21, The Workers Compensation\nAmendment Act. ","index":"00025","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"����� The\nbill implements the majority of recom�mendations from the legislative changes\nmade by the Legislative Review Committee. It also introduces several changes to\nthe corporate governance structure of the Workers Compensation Board that are\ndesigned to increase its financial and operation independence from government. ","index":"00026","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00027","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms. Lisa </b><b><a name=\"_Toc25874818\">Naylor</a></b><b>�(Wolseley):</b>\nI'm pleased to bring forward�sorry�my mistake. Seconded�sorry. ","index":"00028","speaker":"Lisa Naylor"},{"html":"����� I move\nand�seconded by the member for Keewatinook (Mr. Bushie), that Bill 203, The\nClimate&nbsp;and Green Plan Amendment Act (Improved Climate Change Targets and\nEnhanced Ministerial Accountability), be now read a first time. ","index":"00029","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>Motion\npresented.</i></b>� ","index":"00030","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms.\nNaylor:</b> I am pleased to bring forward Bill 203, The Climate and Green Plan\nAmendment Act. ","index":"00031","speaker":"Lisa Naylor"},{"html":"����� This\nbill will strengthen Manitoba's position in fighting the climate crisis. It\nwill hold our government accountable to implementing meaningful targets,\nidentified by the international panel on climate change, to reduce the impact\nof climate change in our province and in our country. ","index":"00032","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(13:40)","index":"00033","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Bill\n203 will also hold the minister accountable to&nbsp;meeting these targets by\ndeducting their salary until the targets have been reached. ","index":"00034","speaker":""},{"html":"Thank you, Madam Speaker.","index":"00035","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? Agreed? <i>[Agreed]\n</i>","index":"00036","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. James</b><b>�<a name=\"_Toc25874822\">Teitsma</a></b><b>�(Chairperson):</b>\nMadam Speaker, I wish to present the First Report of the Standing Committee for\nLegislative Affairs.","index":"00037","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Clerk\n(Ms. Patricia Chaychuk):</b> Your Standing Committee on Legislative Affairs�","index":"00038","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Dispense.","index":"00039","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Dispense.","index":"00040","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Your\nStanding Committee on Legislative Affairs presents the following as its First\nReport.</i>","index":"00041","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>Meetings</i></b>","index":"00042","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Your\nCommittee met on November 27, 2019 at 6:00&nbsp;p.m. in Room 255 of the\nLegislative Building.</i>","index":"00043","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>Matters\nunder Consideration</i></b>","index":"00044","speaker":""},{"html":"<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-family:Symbol\">�<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><i><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Annual Report of Elections Manitoba for the\nyear&nbsp;&nbsp;ending December 31, 2018 including the conduct of the\nSt.&nbsp;Boniface by-election dated July&nbsp;17, 2018</span></i>","index":"00045","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>Committee\nMembership</i></b>","index":"00046","speaker":""},{"html":"<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-family:Symbol\">�<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><i><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Ms. <span style=\"text-transform:uppercase\">Adams</span></span></i>","index":"00047","speaker":""},{"html":"<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-family:Symbol\">�<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><i><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Hon. Mr. <span style=\"text-transform:uppercase\">Cullen</span></span></i>","index":"00048","speaker":""},{"html":"<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-family:Symbol\">�<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;